The paper discusses query evaluation tasks, which are commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence and databases (cs.AI and cs.DB). The use of width parameters such as treewidth and pathwidth suggests a connection to the field of logic and computation (cs.LO), as these parameters are often used in the study of graph algorithms and computational complexity. The mention of deterministic structured NNFs (d-SDNNFs) and OBDDs suggests a connection to the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), as these are common data structures used in knowledge compilation. Finally, the use of lower bounds suggests a connection to the field of computational complexity (cs.CC), as lower bounds are often used to prove limitations on the efficiency of algorithms.
